I rarely write reviews but I had to for this one.  Food: 5 stars! We had the truffle mac and cheese as well as a large Prociutto de parma pizza and it was amazing. Definitely recommend coming here for a good bite.  Drinks: Also 5 stars. In our group of 5 people we ordered wine, margaritas and the manhattan and they were all great!  Service: 5 stars for our inital waitress, 1 star for the last.  This is where our issue was. We had a really nice waitress who took our initial orders and also our repeat orders for about 3 times after. Our last order, which was a second truffle mac and a few drinks we had a different waitress. After that round, we asked for the check and split it where the majority of us paid cash and one person paid on card. We got ready to go and as we were waiting for part of our group to come out from using the restroom, the last waitress who served us approached our group. I didn’t appreciate the tone she took when she asked us if the service was okay. We replied that it was great. I immediately asked her if everything was okay, and she proceeded to explain, with an extremely condescending tone, “well, you had an almost $300 bill (our bill was $239 to be exact) and you only left a $6 tip. We’re working through a pandemic and we work on tips so” and waited for us to “properly” tip her. This is something I can completely understand as I have also been working through the pandemic and regardless of this virus have always tipped my servers for great service. Of course this was a miscommunication between us when we paid the bill thinking that the gratuity was included and that was our mistake. But the tone and attitude that the waitress had with us was uncalled for and showed the type of waitress she is, at least to me.  I did not appreciate her attitude towards us at all and would have given 5 stars had she not approached us in such a rude manner, as if we’d owed her something. I loved everything else but I highly doubt I’ll be back, after being hounded by a waitress that wasn’t even our waitress the entire time over a miscommunication on our bill.  We did end up tipping  because the service, food and drinks were great up until that moment, and it’s something we would have done regardless.

I took a bite of their mac and cheese burger along with ther Bedford plank burger (added some bacon to it) because why not?? & I wasn't disappointed. This place was definitely worth the trip. This review is specificity to the owner,  We come to the restaurant once or twice a week since we live a cross the street. The food is ok The drinks are ok too. The staff are great. To our surprise, when we got back the credit card receipt to sign and leave a tip we see a SVC charge. Let me explain, SvC charge is a charge that is usually paid by the restaurant not the client. So, if your bill is 200 now add additional $8 since SvC charges between 2-4% depending on the card your using. I think it’s simply disgusting to charge your customer additional fees that were not disclosed from the beginning. We told our server about our concern with this charge. She explained the restaurant has now transferred the fee to the client instead of paying it. Listen sweetie, we have all been slammed by this pandemic not just the restaurants so putting fees on other human beings is not the answer. We support the restaurants, will keep eating out and we don’t mind to pay a extra dollar for a dish, but don’t make us pay your fees. NOT COOL
